## Applied: lib/libftp_client_ryu/adapter/include/ryu_ftp_connection_diag.h

New diagnostic API:

```c
void ryu_ftp_diag_set_transfer(uint32_t transfer_id,
                               const char *engine,
                               const char *direction);
void ryu_ftp_diag_clear_transfer(void);
void ryu_ftp_diag_dump(const char *phase);
csp_conn_t *ryu_ftp_diag_connect(const char *site,
                                 uint8_t prio,
                                 uint8_t dest,
                                 uint8_t dport,
                                 uint32_t timeout,
                                 uint32_t opts);
int ryu_ftp_diag_close(const char *site, csp_conn_t *conn);
```

When `FTP_RYU_CONN_DIAG` is not defined, the transfer/dump functions compile
as inline no-ops and no connect/close wrapper declarations are exposed.

## Applied: lib/libftp_client_ryu/adapter/src/ryu_ftp_connection_diag.c

New diagnostic implementation guarded entirely by:

```c
#ifdef FTP_RYU_CONN_DIAG
```

It records:

- `csp_connect` call/return with transfer ID, destination, port, timeout, opts
- `csp_close` call/return with return code
- connection pointer and connection-table index from `csp_conn_get_array()`
- outer `CONN_*` state and `RDP_*` state
- src/dst/dport/sport/flags
- `age_ms` and `RDP_CLOSE_WAIT` residency
- table aggregate `csp_conn_max=<N> open=<count>`

It does not modify CSP/RDP state, packet layout, timeout values, or transfer
data.

## Applied: lib/libftp_client_ryu/port/client/src/ftpnew_client.c

Added diagnostic macros:

```c
#ifdef FTP_RYU_CONN_DIAG
#include "ryu_ftp_connection_diag.h"
#define FTPNEW_CSP_CONNECT(site, prio, dest, dport, timeout, opts) \
    ryu_ftp_diag_connect((site), (prio), (dest), (dport), (timeout), (opts))
#define FTPNEW_CSP_CLOSE(site, conn) ryu_ftp_diag_close((site), (conn))
#else
#define FTPNEW_CSP_CONNECT(site, prio, dest, dport, timeout, opts) \
    csp_connect((prio), (dest), (dport), (timeout), (opts))
#define FTPNEW_CSP_CLOSE(site, conn) csp_close((conn))
#endif
```

Replaced Ryu client call sites only:

- `csp_connect(...)` in `ftpnew_upload()` -> `FTPNEW_CSP_CONNECT("ftpnew_upload", ...)`
- `csp_connect(...)` in `ftpnew_download()` -> `FTPNEW_CSP_CONNECT("ftpnew_download", ...)`
- `csp_close(state->conn)` in `ftpnew_done()` -> `FTPNEW_CSP_CLOSE("ftpnew_done", state->conn)`
- `csp_close(state->conn)` in `ftpnew_data()` error path -> `FTPNEW_CSP_CLOSE("ftpnew_data_error", state->conn)`

